<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="731" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Carbo</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Ecuador</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-24"><hi rend="italic">June 24,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: Having brought to the knowledge
                            of my Government the contents of the various communications which your
                            Department has addressed to me relative to the state of war which exists
                            between the United States of America and the Kingdom of Spain, I have
                            received instructions to state to you that the Government of Ecuador,
                            while deploring the armed contest between two powers with which it
                            maintains relations of good friendship and commerce, declares its
                            absolute neutrality in accordance with the law of nations.</p>
                        <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">L. F. Carbo.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>